Builds NCA Code from ui Elements

Source: R/NCA_Server.R
nca_builder.Rd

Takes the current analysis in the state object and creates the code to run the analysis

Usage

nca_builder(state)

Arguments

state

NCA state from NCA_fetch_state()

Value

NCA state with the NCA for the current analysis built. This defines the following elements of the current analysis:

  • code_sa Source code to run the analysis (includes loading packages, data wranling, etc)

  • code Same as code_sa except it assumes all packages have been loaded

  • code_fetch Runs the analysis assuming all dependent objects like datasets are currently defined in the workspace

  • code_components List of the code components with the following elements:

    • code_previous Code from other upstream modules that this analysis depends on (e.g. datasets being loaded and any data wrangling.)

    • code_ana_only Only the analysis assuming any upstream objects, such as the source dataset, have been defined

    • code_fg_ind_obs Generate all plots for individual observations

    • code_fg_ind_obs_subset Regenerate a subset of the plots for individual observations

    • code_tb_ind_obs Generate table of individual observations

    • code_tb_ind_obs_flags Generate table of flagged points

    • code_tb_ind_params Generate table of individual parameters

  • objs Mapping of object generic names to names used by the analysis stored in the "names" element of the following elements:

    • ds NCA dataset

    • rm Route map

    • drec Dose records

    • ints Analysis intervals

    • dose PKNCA dosing object (from: PKNCA::PKNCAdose())

    • data PKNCA data object (from: PKNCA::PKNCAdata())

    • conc PKNCA concentration object (from: PKNCA::PKNCAconc())

    • res NCA results (from: PKNCA::pk.nca)

    • ds_flags Dataframe containing flagging details

    • col_map List mapping columns in source dataset to columns needed in PKNCA

    • flag_map List contianing mapping information from short names used in flagging to other details

    • fg_ind_obs Figures of individual observations

    • tb_ind_obs Table(s) of individual observations

    • tb_ind_obs_flags Table(s) of flagged datapoints

    • tb_ind_params Table(s) of individual parameters

# We need a module variables to be defined
sess_res = NCA_test_mksession()
